{"1368–":"1368–Overleden","1368–Male":"1368–Overleden","1370–Female":"1370–Overleden","1386–1472":"1386–1472","1394–Female":"1394–Overleden","1310–Male":"1310–Overleden","–1369":"–1369","1369":"1369","1368":"1368","1388":"1388","1310":"1310","1386":"1386","1472":"1472","1394":"1394","1370":"1370","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Essex, England":"Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Flanders, Belgium":"Vlaanderen, België","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England"},"en":{"1368–":"1368–Deceased","1368–Male":"1368–Deceased","1370–Female":"1370–Deceased","1386–1472":"1386–1472","1394–Female":"1394–Deceased","1310–Male":"1310–Deceased","–1369":"–1369","1369":"1369","1368":"1368","1388":"1388","1310":"1310","1386":"1386","1472":"1472","1394":"1394","1370":"1370","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England, United Kingdom","Flanders, Belgium":"Flanders, Belgium","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bulstrode","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Bulstrode (Bucks)."],"variants":[{"name":"Bostridge","meanings":["English: variant of   Bulstrode  ."]},{"name":"Bolstridge","meanings":["English (Midlands): variant of <b>Bulstrode</b>, a habitational name from Bulstrode in Buckinghamshire, meaning ‘bull marsh’ from Old English <i>bula</i> ‘bull’ + <i>strōd</i> ‘marshy land’."]},{"name":"Boustred","meanings":["English:  see  Bulstrode  ."]},{"name":"Boulstridge","meanings":["English:  see  Bulstrode  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Bulstrode was born in 1368, in Essex, England, United Kingdom as the son of John Bulstrode I and Margaret Montfort Bulstrode. He married Agne Knyffe in 1388. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in Flanders, Belgium."},"et":{"1368–":"1368–Surnud","1368–Male":"1368–Surnud","1370–Female":"1370–Surnud","1386–1472":"1386–1472","1394–Female":"1394–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","–1369":"–1369","1369":"1369","1368":"1368","1388":"1388","1310":"1310","1386":"1386","1472":"1472","1394":"1394","1370":"1370","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Essex, England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Flanders, Belgium":"Vlaanderen, Belgia","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1368–":"1368–Kuollut","1368–Male":"1368–Kuollut","1370–Female":"1370–Kuollut","1386–1472":"1386–1472","1394–Female":"1394–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","–1369":"–1369","1369":"1369","1368":"1368","1388":"1388","1310":"1310","1386":"1386","1472":"1472","1394":"1394","1370":"1370","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Essex, England":"Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Flanders, Belgium":"Vlaanderen, Belgia","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"